I bet it would be Lewis Miller, Ariella Chezar, Oscar Mora, Tulipina, Summer Robbins or Ingrid Carozzi of Tin Can Studios. 🌷

And guess where they studied or taught their craft? It was Calvert Crary’s FlowerSchoolNY and FlowerSchool LA. 🌼

And now for the first time, Crary, who owned shops before running his U.S.floral schools, has written a must-have book for any flower lover called, “Flower School: A Practical Guide to the Art of Flower Arranging.”💐

The word practical resonates here. Because Crary has been described as what George Balanchine was to ballet, he knows how to teach the fundamentals without being, well, too flowery. We think of him as the Dr. Fauci of flowers - accessible, honest and knowledgeable. 🌿

You become a scientist in his floral lab where you learn step-by-step all the fundamentals you really need to know. Among the facts we loved to learn? Cut from your gardens early in the morning for maximum blooms otherwise the stem will think it has been killed. Calla Lilies will rot in too much water so only put two inches of water in a vase. Hydrate tulips before arranging for several hours. 
 Great tips right?

Plus as a bonus, you get interviews with the greats on how they design including Kiana Underwood, Victoria Ahn and Olivier Giugni. 

Read more on our website story and definitely consider buying this book. One of our favorites.🌺

